WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.200
Hello and welcome back. In the previous video, I showed you how to add DeepSeek as a model for

00:00:05.200 --> 00:00:14.210
OpenClaw. I later found out that DeepSeek version 4 Pro is available. In this video, I will show

00:00:14.210 --> 00:00:21.330
you how I upgraded the DeepSeek model to version 4 Pro. I had asked ChatGPT how to upgrade

00:00:24.380 --> 00:00:34.480
and it gave a reply. In Telegram, I gave the instruction saying I want to change to DeepSeek

00:00:34.480 --> 00:00:45.780
version 4 pro. I then copied the chat gpt output and pasted it into telegram

00:01:10.190 --> 00:01:15.470
open claw replied saying it will check the configurations and also list down what it

00:01:15.470 --> 00:01:33.380
needs to do. It then made the changes and verified the result and gave a summary of what it did.

00:01:35.300 --> 00:01:41.540
It also reminded me to restart open claw for the new primary model to take effect and ask if it

00:01:41.540 --> 00:01:47.780
should do that and I replied yes. If it had not restarted you would have to use

00:01:47.780 --> 00:01:54.500
this command: open claw gateway restart. After restarting I cleared the telegram

00:01:54.500 --> 00:02:07.820
chat history and started a new session. I then listed the models using the command:

00:02:07.820 --> 00:02:18.910
open claw models list, and it showed me the list of the models. I can see that it

00:02:18.910 --> 00:02:24.830
It has successfully upgraded the primary model to Deep Seek version 4 Pro and made it the

00:02:24.830 --> 00:02:26.190
default model.

00:02:26.190 --> 00:02:33.270
Also note that the fallback model is now GPT 5.4.

00:02:33.270 --> 00:02:39.680
Back in Telegram, I asked it, what model are you on?

00:02:39.680 --> 00:02:43.700
And it replies, Deep Seek version 4 Pro.

00:02:43.700 --> 00:02:45.820
That's all for this video.

00:02:45.820 --> 00:02:46.760
Thanks for watching.

